The paper deals with information theoretic concepts such as degrees of freedom and capacity, indicating that it is likely to belong to the cs.IT (Information Theory) sub-category. The focus on cellular networks suggests that it could also belong to cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) or cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). The use of optimization techniques and the mention of convexity suggest that it could belong to cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) or cs.CC (Computational Complexity).
